lead_paragraph: Iowa, ranked No. 1 and the Big Ten champion, goes for its 21st national team title at the N.C.A.A. championships, which begins Thursday in St. Louis. The Hawkeyes, 21-1 in dual meets, are one of five teams to qualify nine wrestlers for the event. Minnesota, ranked No. 8, won last year’s championship and is seeking its fourth national title in the past eight years.
